uite simple:\n\nxdebug.mode=debug\nxdebug.start_with_request=yes\nxdebug.client_host=host.docker.internal\nxdebug.remote_port=9003\n\nand it works very well',0,'1','','comment',0,0),(27,999,'ice6','ice6@live.cn','http://gravatar.com/ice6','172.69.34.94','2021-01-22 05:08:44','2021-01-22 10:08:44','https://xdebug.org/docs/all_settings',0,'0','','comment',26,0),(28,999,'Dav Iru','virtudavi99@gmail.com','','172.69.42.12','2021-01-29 14:54:30','2021-01-29 19:54:30','There\'s a misstatement here: \n\n\"setup remote debugging for XDebug so that PHPStorm can connect to it and set breakpoints\"\n\nPHPStorm doesn\'t connect to XDebug, XDebug connects to PHPStorm, and you set breakpoints in the code files in PHPStorm whether XDebug is hooked up or not.',0,'spam','','comment',0,0),(29,999,'laue.dancu','laue.dancu@gmail.com','','141.101.97.56','2021-02-06 13:43:14','2021-02-06 18:43:14','Dude, you\'re a wizard! I had trouble with your host update script not updating hosts, but setting the host manually to the value of wsl hostname -I did the trick. Thanks!',0,'1','','comment',0,0),(30,999,'Malkom','jerom.bonnier@gmail.com','','108.162.229.164','2021-05-03 10:02:28','2021-05-03 15:02:28','You have to install .NET Core  v3.1',0,'0','','comment',24,0);
